OL,3,CCare home director 'upset and
OL,4,Cdisappointed' by Covid breach claims
OL,6,FIt has been alleged that during the
OL,7,FCovid-19 pandemic some staff did not
OL,8,Fwear face masks or PPE, that others
OL,9,Fcarried on working after testing
OL,10,Fpositive for the virus, and that test
OL,11,Fresults were ignored.
OL,13,FAlison Longhorn, area coroner for
OL,14,FDevon, Plymouth and Torbay, is holding
OL,15,Finquests into the deaths of William
OL,16,FWilkinson, 102, Doris Lockett, 92, Roy
OL,17,FGilliam, 96, Jean Hartley, 81, Susan
OL,18,FSkinner, 70, Ronald Bampfylde, 92, and
OL,19,FStdanislawa Koch, 93.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/16
