OL,3,CCare home director 'upset and
OL,4,Cdisappointed' by Covid breach claims
OL,6,FMr Neal said the contingency plan
OL,7,Fshould have swung into action
OL,8,Fimmediately.
OL,10,FThe inquest heard that, two days
OL,11,Flater, the Care Quality Commission
OL,12,Finspected the nursing home, but the
OL,13,Fpositive test wasn't raised.
OL,15,FOther staff alleged the manager,
OL,16,FJoanne Burchell, had not sent sick
OL,17,Fstaff home due to shortages and had
OL,18,Fignored positive lateral flow tests
OL,19,Fresults.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/16
