OL,6,F"If Jo has retained people at work
OL,7,Fwhen they should have gone home then
OL,8,Fthat is absolutely unacceptable.
OL,10,F"I did assure Jemma when she whistle-
OL,11,Fblowed directly to me that I would
OL,12,Fhave dealt with these matters but we
OL,13,Fwere in the eye of the storm."
OL,15,FThe inquest heard that Mrs Burchell
OL,16,Fand the nurse who refused to wear a
OL,17,Fmask were both arrested and
OL,18,Finterviewed by the police, but no
OL,19,Ffurther action was taken against them.
